<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>Bright Future is committed to protecting your personal information and privacy. This policy outlines how we collect, use, store, and safeguard your data in accordance with New Zealand’s Privacy Act 2020.</p>

<h4>1. Information We Collect</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Personal identification (e.g. name, date of birth, passport number)</li>
    <li>Contact details (e.g. email, phone number, address)</li>
    <li>Immigration history and education background</li>
    <li>Supporting documents for visa or study applications</li>
</ul>

<h4>2. How We Use Your Information</h4>
<ul>
    <li>To assess your eligibility for immigration or education pathways</li>
    <li>To lodge visa, study, or residency applications on your behalf</li>
    <li>To communicate with immigration authorities or educational institutions</li>
    <li>To provide updates and support during your application process</li>
</ul>

<h4>3. Disclosure of Information</h4>
<p>We do not sell or share your information with third parties except when required by law or when submitting applications on your behalf to relevant authorities.</p>

<h4>4. Data Security</h4>
<p>All personal data is stored securely and accessed only by authorized personnel. We use encryption, secure storage, and access control to protect your information.</p>

<h4>5. Access and Correction</h4>
<p>You have the right to access and correct your personal information. Please contact us if you wish to review or amend the data we hold.</p>

<h4>6. Retention</h4>
<p>We retain personal information only as long as necessary for the purpose it was collected or as required by law.</p>

<h4>7. Contact Us</h4>
<p>If you have any questions or concerns about your privacy, please email us at <strong>shaun@brightfuture.co.nz</strong>.</p>